gmap.adr_address: 91 Rainey St Ste 120, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.formatted_address: 91 Rainey St Ste 120, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.name: Anthem

reviews.text: Had a great time here showing some friends from out of town Rainey. We shared the poo poo platter which was more than enough food. Everything was very good. Staff was very friendly and regularly checked on us. Get the Mai Tai drink, it comes in a to go Chinese cup. Will come back and try other food options.
One of the best food spots I’ve tried in Downtown Austin hands down! Y’all have to try the pupu platter, it was DIVINE. The drinks were great and the bartender was very pleasant. 10/10

Customer service was on point! All else was a bonus

We arrived on a busy spring break afternoon. We were seated quickly and the host was acknowledging and thorough which was reassuring. We were able to sit on the outdoor deck which was great for people watching. Considering the time of day, it was pretty loud outdoors but that was expected so it wasn’t a bother. The views are pleasing. Our server was friendly and attentive which was a perfect reflection of the service we received since being greeted at the front door.

We came for drinks, another bonus was the weekend happy hour. $1 off draft beer! Plus select cocktails for just $7 from 3PM to 6:30 p.m.

Overall worth the visit if you are visiting Rainey St or Austin in general!
Stopped by for lunch & a drink. Service was great. Aloha burger was really good? Ceviche was pretty good as well.

As visitors to Austin, Anthem was our first taste of legendary local cuisine.  Awesome atmosphere, impressively creative menu, and a drink selection to satisfy any palate!  If you get a chance to come here, do it!  *MAKE SURE TO ASK FOR SHANE AS YOUR SERVER, if you can*
He had wonderful recommendations and was very welcoming and hospitable!

name: Arlo Grey
address: 111 E Cesar Chavez St Austin TX 78701 USA

gmap.adr_address: 111 E Cesar Chavez St, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.formatted_address: 111 E Cesar Chavez St, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.name: Arlo Grey by Kristen Kish

reviews.text: Food was all fantastic.  The combinations of spices and flavors were so surprising.  Ordered items I was not sure how they would taste but they were all lovely.  Even just the grilled/smoked sourdough had so much flavor.  Plates are small but shareable so try multiple.

We had a fantastic dining experience at Arlo Grey. A week night reservation is definitely the way to go. Our server, Spencer, was very down to earth and knowledgeable about every item on the menu. All of the plates are small and shareable. The sour dough bread is to die for and the tomato salad. Both pasta dishes were delicious, I literally could have eaten both of them myself. The jalapeño margarita was spicy and perfect and the lemon tart is a must. We can’t wait to go back.

Came to town and was excited about trying this restaurant from one of my top chef favorites, although unfortunately I am highly disappointed.
The drinks were good, tea thyme and rainbow old fashioned.
For apps we had the sourdough bread (can’t go wrong with grilled sourdough) and tomato salad. The tomatoes on the salad were soggy and tired.
For main we had the burger and poached halibut. My husband who is a burger and mashed potato connoisseur didn’t even finish his burger and was clearly disappointed and I took a few bites of the halibut only to be disheartened by the jelly-like skin left on the fish and the strong after taste that wasn’t “fresh” as advertised.
The overall atmosphere was not what I expected based off of open table photos. The restaurant is open directly to the lobby and the overall decor has a “pop up” feel with temporary like or thrown together items.
Again, I had high hopes for this place, but it boils down to the physical appearance not living up to my thrill about eating at one of Kristens restaurants as well as the food not living up to my celebrity chef expectations. I still love Kristen, but dissatisfied with my experience at this restaurant.

PS- they automatically add 19% gratuity

Tasty food but the service was extremely mediocre. Our waitress wasn't familiar familiar the wine list - which was ok,  but the fact that she forgot we were waiting on her to find out about a bottle of wine, and went on to serving our appetizer was weird. The worst part was, she was pushing us far too hard to get dessert even though we were struggling to finish our meal. Overall, the experience was very average. I would expect a much better experience for how much we paid.

Small plates, EXTREMELY delicious, but equivalently expensive. If you're looking for a  gourmet tasting style meal, this place is great.  Atmosphere is very stylish. Service is impeccable. Bougie is a good descriptor (in the good sense if you like that sort of stuff!)

gmap.adr_address: 1315 W 6th St, Austin, TX 78703, USA
gmap.name: Bar Peached

reviews.text: Bar staff was amazing. Incredibly busy but still found time to be attentive and offer suggestions. The fish tacos was the star of the night for me. Their house margarita is good, but spicy! Would definitely come back if I’m ever visiting again. The outdoor seating area looked ideal for groups too!

Been here a couple times. The food is good quality and above average, nothing to write home about though. The service is not very good, I’m guessing because they already add a 5% tip to every bill so they aren’t really trying to impress. The drink are good and unique. The atmosphere is where this place shines, really nice outdoor seating and cute indoor seating.

Social Hour at Bar Peached is a must. Fish tacos, charred Brussels sprouts and social burger are our faves. Their spicy margarita is excellent. Also try the big breezy and the yoga&chill. Both very light but satisfying cocktails. They have super friendly staff and big fans that make sitting outside bearable in the hot Texas summer days.
The food was absolutely delicious! It is served family style so 1 entree is meant to be shared with everyone having a little bit. 10/10 and highly recommend to family/friends.

I’ve been looking forward to trying this place for a long time and we finally made it in tonight! The staff is super friendly and we had the best service from our server Noon! (Apologize if the spelling is wrong) the food was great and the happy hour “Social Hour” menu has great deals! 10/10 recommend the “margarita de peached” it was the perfect level of spicy and refreshing. Will definitely be coming back for the tacos and drinks!

gmap.adr_address: 406 Walsh St, Austin, TX 78703, USA
gmap.name: Better Half Coffee & Cocktails

reviews.text: The food was very delicious. I got the spicy chicken sandwich on biscuit. The service was really good, we didn't wait long for our food and they brought it right out. It was a little loud for us inside, so we ate outside.

We ordered the hash browns, the pastrami toast, fries, and a mimosa. The hash browns were terrible.  The gravy is overpowering and too salty. The sweet notes clash with the potatoes in the hashbrowns to make an overall horrible dish. The mimosa was absolutely terrible as well - 0 flavor and super watered down. The toast was fine but nothing special about it. The meat was the only redeeming quality and even that wasn’t amazing. The fries were the only “yummy” food and even those were 5$. If you still want to come here for some reason do not order what we did.

Don’t let the pictures fool you.

This place is perfect if you don’t want lots of loud and pretentious youngsters just spending extra cash to hang out and be loud and pretentious. Bordering on being low-key, they have select but consistently prepared select dishes with the right amount of uniqueness but without all the froufrou. So glad to see a nice cafe/restaurant/bar not overrun by self-absorbed (but outwardly projecting) individuals. You can enjoy good food and good drinks here with your friends.

Delicious biscuits and lattes here. I am planning to go back to try some of the other things but each time I'm there I can't help but get that biscuit!

I also got a really cute t-shirt there.

This place is great! Loved the iced latte, cauliflower tots and veggie cheese burger. I didn’t jive with the first dish I ordered and the management was super sweet & understanding and got me something I loved. Would recommend to others for sure.

name: Black Star Co-Op
address: 7020 Easy Wind Dr Austin TX 78752 USA

gmap.adr_address: 7020 Easy Wind Dr, Austin, TX 78752, USA
gmap.formatted_address: 7020 Easy Wind Dr, Austin, TX 78752, USA
gmap.name: Black Star Co-op

reviews.text:
Excellent food, awesome beer. You can never go wrong with the Black Star burger, or the fried chicken sandwich. Also, the fish and chips are pretty darn good.

They have one of the best sour beer you can get, The Waterloo, but don't ignore the Vulcan either; another great beer.

One of my favorite burger joints in Austin.

The food was good. The service was horrible. The counter guy was extremely rude. He interrupted us while we were placing the order. Then, end up by messing the order anyway.  No one wants to pay 150 dollars out of their pocket and deal with this rude person. We were on a time crunch, and could not leave and had to eat. The fries were truly amazing.

Again, it would really help to remove unhappy staff.

04/10/2021 - Place still open during COVID. In dining available. There are a lot of outside tables now. Recommend for social distancing. But on peak hours there are a lot of people together so be careful.

Great home brew beer, food is exceptional and location is perfect. But, do not buy the buffalo wings, these are delicious but are so small, you will be disappointed. Not worth the $10.

Parking is free, the train and bus station are right in front of it, perfect for going to Downtown.

The menu change during the day so make sure to see the menu before heading to this location.

Board games are available in this location.

You can become a member for a fee and get good perks out of it.

I personally didn't go inside. A friend got a glass of wine and a beer here and she enjoyed both. Outdoor seating was nice in a little park setting. They're very dog friendly and there was an acoustic band playing. Really chill hangout.

One of the best "better" burgers in Austin.  Plain and simple.

It's a bit hard to find from Lamar because it's semi-hidden in the Midtown Commons apartment complex.  Like the Triangle and most other new Austin developments, there's retail and restaurants on the ground floor.

Decided to drop in here tonight because the burger came highly recommended.  I'm definitely glad I tried it.  The burger is deceptively small.  It looks like a smaller burger, but the density of the high quality burger patty combined with their bun makes it more than a meal.  Don't forget their fries, which were described to me as English style chips.  The fries look like flattened steak fries and are exceptionally crispy.  I'm not sure what the seasoning is, but it's strangely addictive.

Black Star has a huge variety of beers for the drinkers.  For the non-drinkers, they have a variety of canned and bottled soft drinks, although no fountain drinks.

Being a co-op, the service is friendly and obviously takes a lot of pride in their pub.  The quality of the food and the service both show that.

name: Bufalina Pizza
address: 1519 E Cesar Chavez St #200 Austin TX 78702 USA

gmap.adr_address: 6555 Burnet Rd #100, Austin, TX 78757-2839, USA
gmap.name: Bufalina Due

reviews.text: Some of the beat pizza I’ve ever had.  The sauce on the Margherita pizza tasted fresh and vibrant and was a pleasure to eat. The dough was light and airy and had the perfect crunch. Also the setup of this restaurant is great. I loved seeing pizzas getting put in the big brick oven due to the fact it was in the middle of the restaurant. Overall a very pleasant experience

We are glad we've found this gem.Everything was perfect. The entire restaurant team worked like a well-oiled machine.

The food was the OMG kind... simply delicious.

Our orders consisted of the Mozzarella plate, Oven-Baked Squash, Margarita and Red Pie Pizzas.

The Mozzarella was fresh and the pesto dressing was superb.

The squash was baked just right and loved the cheese accompaniment.

The Pizzas were worthy of several wows....both were bursting with flavor, especially the Red Pie.

The service was top notch. The atmosphere was very lively, lovely and casual. The prices are more than reasonable for this high quality food.

I highly recommend this restaurant and it is worth the drive no matter where you live in Austin.

Great pizza, with a slightly charred crust like you'd want from a wood fired oven. Caesar salad was decent, without too much of a sardine taste, if at all.
Tirimisu was interesting... I've never had one with a salted butter taste. Not enough espresso in it either.
Absolutely DELICIOUS pizza and awesome wine selection! The appetizers were incredible too! I’ll definitely be back. And bringing friends with me next time!
Amazing dough. People were really nice and informed. Great happy hour, 1/2 off pies and $5 wine

name: Central Standard
address: 1603 S Congress Ave Austin TX 78704 USA

gmap.adr_address: 1603 S Congress Ave, Austin, TX 78704, USA
gmap.formatted_address: 1603 S Congress Ave, Austin, TX 78704, USA
gmap.name: Central Standard

reviews.text: It left a lot to be desired. We had reservations and high hopes because the host staff was so kind. It was a long wait for us to be acknowledged by our server and that set the stage for the rest of the brunch. Long wait times for ordering, drinks and food. Our water was also not refilled which made everything a little more painful.  The server explained they were short staffed so I wanted to sympathize but then the food came out. It was two cold plates and one steaming hot plate. We also could witness the larger parties getting a lot of attention which made everything a little frustrating since we couldn’t get anyone to stop by the table. I really wish the wait or food was worth it but will not be trying again.

Service was great and our waitress was excellent, food was not the best, but wasn't bad either, the cheese broccoli with pizza bread was AMAZING. Great variety of cocktails and great location near downtown Austin.

Drinks were excellent, though a little pricey. Sadly, the drinks were the stand out item we had for brunch.

I had the french toast, it was soggy and way too sticky sweet. Just a lump of moosh on my plate. Disappointing. My companion had the shrimp and grits I'd just been to NOLA so maybe my standards were too high, but they were just ok. Really wanted to like this place.

We really enjoyed our brunch. The oysters were amazing and the food all around was good. Our waitress missed a couple things....never brought another water glass (we were 1 short), food item got forgotten....but she was very friendly. We had a friend with some allergies and she was patient and worked with her to figure out food options. Overall though we were pleased.

Just stopped by to order drinks with a friend. Unfortunately our waitress was very strange and gave me two drinks with flies in them. When we pointed out the second time (80% sure she gave me the exact same drink back) she said "the resturant can't control that and there was nothing she could do". Didn't even apologize. Girl BYE. We won't be back. :)

gmap.adr_address: 1200 W 6th St, Austin, TX 78703, USA
gmap.name: Clark's Oyster Bar

reviews.text: What a gem. Clarks exceeded all my expectations. Popped in there to grab a few oysters but ended up having a full meal. The servers were also so incredible. One wrote me a full list of where to explore in Austin!! If you are in town I highly suggest checking it out and trying a range of oysters and the lobster Mac n cheese

Spectacular. Amazing. Divine. Fresh.

All of these describe Clark’s Oyster Bar and more. Everything everyone at my table had was divine.  From the best omelette ever to the amazing salad garnish and dressing.

Definitely go here. No question.

Absolutely incredible. Clark’s has the best oysters Austin has to offer. Also, check out the catches of the day (the rotating fish menu). We had the Branzino with a chili oil sauce—perfectly cooked, not too much added flavor but the right amount of seasoning. Get reservations.

Brought my boyfriend here for his birthday last month and we had a wonderful experience. We sat on the patio, ordered the jumbo shrimp cocktail, a variety of oysters, the mac n cheese, some dessert, and drinks. It was all delicious and the service was friendly.

Clark’s is one of my favorite for a leisurely brunch spot, especially during patio weather! Service and food has always been consistently great. Love their rotating selection of fresh oysters and tasty cocktails 👍

gmap.adr_address: 2027 Anchor Ln, Austin, TX 78723, USA
gmap.name: Contigo

reviews.text:
This place is so cozy and cute. Delicious food and drinks with a relaxing and welcoming ambiance. I had the most amazing experience one Sunday evening. My server’s name was Raven and he did a impeccable job of walking me through the menu and recommending their delicious specialty frozen painkiller.

In addition I had the pork belly appetizer which also was prepared with delicacy.

I will definitely be back to visit Raven and enjoy another marvelous dinner at Contigo.

5 Stars all around.
We had the quail, fish, and charred avocado. The food and drinks were all perfect. The quail was extremely good. Our service was also terrific making the entire experience wonderful. We will be back.

I've always had a great experience at Contigo. The staff is friendly and attentive, the food is fantastic, and the atmosphere is relaxing and comfortable whether your in a large party or on a dinner date. Extra bonus points for their large parking lot, that's such a variety nowadays in the city.

We really liked their guava margaritas! We had the rabbit gnocchi and the burger. Both were pretty good but a little pricey. We would highly recommend the fried green beans though. The aioli that comes with it is awesome!
Outlandishly good. Every single thing we ordered was delicious. Rabbit gnocchi? Incredible. Guava margaritas? Incredible. Enjoy y'all

name: Culinary Dropout
address: 11721 Rock Rose Ave #100 Austin TX 78758 USA

gmap.adr_address: 11721 Rock Rose Ave Ste #100, Austin, TX 78758, USA
gmap.formatted_address: 11721 Rock Rose Ave Ste #100, Austin, TX 78758, USA
gmap.name: Culinary Dropout

reviews.text: Really nice atmosphere and friendly staff. We did see a Karen here in front of us being impatient. Not sure what she expected when coming on a Saturday afternoon. The staff was super friendly and handled her well. It was my first time eating here and I enjoyed it. I ordered the fried chicken. It was very crunch and moist! They also have a good drink selection selection. I will for sure come back to eat again

Atmosphere is great. We got outdoor seating and it was such a cute place to gather with friends. Didn't feel crowded and the waitress was super attentive and nice. Had the mule which was absolutely delicious and refreshing. No flavor was overpowering the other. Perfect ratio of flavor. For food had the Caesar salad with avocado and it was really good. Lettuce tasted and looked fresh and the avocados were perfectly ripe. The dressing was on point too.

Birthday dinner was perfect. Every item we ordered was excellent. Don't miss their Pretzels and Fondue. They are so good! The burgers, Roasted Salmon and the veg lasagna must try.Patio dining was nice and cool, thanks to their mist fans. My only issue was that the chairs and the floor weren't very clean.

Scratch kitchens and some cheaper beer and spirits options sonata bad. The food was pretty good but not superior considering the food all over Austin. It was a little pricey but nothing outrageous. You'll leave thinking hey that was pretty good but maybe should have been a little cheaper for the product provided.the service was good albeit we had a trainee so that was ok. The environment is real laid back, super casual. All of the servers are young and wear fashionable clothing from home and they are all trendy 20 somethings with a smile and a joke ready to go so all was well.

Culinary Dropout. Easily the best restaurant in the domain in terms of food, quality and service. It doesn’t matter where you sit. The bar staff is just as friendly and youthful as the server staff. The food is on point. The ribs, burgers, chicken, soups, apps, etc. I remember one time they didn’t cook my burger all the way through, however. I asked for a new one. I can not tell you how many times restaurants have dropped the ball when it comes to re cooking your food. Other places are usually rude and take so long you lose your appetite. I was so surprised when I received an apology from the manager and my re-cooked, juicy burger in a timely manner. This is honestly one of the only places I can  consistently recommend if you’re looking for a quality restaurant in the Domain. Downsides? They’re always packed (Can you really blame them for that?), and they don’t have any nutritional information. There’s actually a thread on their facebook page that started over 5 years ago with people asking for updates on this. Maybe one day they’ll release it. Till then, I wish I could give this place 6 stars.

gmap.adr_address: 9333 Research Blvd Suite A600, Austin, TX 78759, USA
gmap.formatted_address: 9333 Research Blvd Suite A600, Austin, TX 78759, USA
gmap.name: Dave & Buster's

reviews.text: March 2021-Enjoyed my visit here as always. Everyone was pleasant and respectful. The food was slamming! Waitress was on point, except her supervisors kept coming by to see if we were good. That was a good thing, just started to get a bit annoying. Love the big screens!! The crane game is addictive! _____2019-Plenty packed on Saturday, but everyone was respectful and helpful...so were the patrons. 5 stars

I misclicked on rating originally. We came here for a birthday get together and my son had a blast. Our waiter (Alex) was super attentive and helpful with getting us our food and drinks and updating us. I appreciated the extra effort he took to recommend a drink which I ended up loving. Can't wait to come back here.

The staff is the sweetest from beginning to end. The food is yummy albeit pricey and cocktails are good too. I was a kid again for a little while. If you are lucky enough to have Toni as your server she is so sweet and funny. Overall I recommend for a date night or a family night ❤  my husband is mad cause I beat him on all the games

We went just for games and no food and had a blast. I'm not really into arcade games but I found several that I enjoyed! Pro tip: We went on Wednesday so all the games were half priced so $30 went incredibly far for 2 people!
The reason not a 5 was it took 10 min after we was seated before the server ask if anybody has help us. We where getting ready to leave. After that food came out quickly. Plus the food was good.

name: DuMont Down Low
address: 214 W 4th St Suite B Austin TX 78701 USA

gmap.adr_address: 214 W 4th St Suite B, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.formatted_address: 214 W 4th St Suite B, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.name: DuMont's Down Low

reviews.text: Very cool place! Good, chill vibes for a late night drink. Excellent cocktails. The Blanche was a group fave!
I love drink there, they so good. You should try Lavender bee, it’s so good. Also, Sunday happy hours amazing, just $ 5-8 select drinks

This is hands down one of my favorite places to ever go it's got that cool 1940s vibe it's underground basements. The whiskey is absolutely amazing with it with a eccentric unique great selection it's always super comfortable the atmosphere is always dim and just classy music's great bartenders are super kind and amazing and very well talented and can make an amazing cocktail hands down one of my absolutely favorite bars ever

Atmosphere is dark and moody in the best way, and the music playing was fire. Drinks were great, nothing life changing, but they were worth the money. Going on a weeknight was perfect. It wasn’t too busy, and I felt safe COVID-wise. I’d love to go back sometime soon, and maybe bring a few others with me. Service was very attentive A+
Really cool place!  Great drinks, awesome friendly service!  Highly recommend.  I had the Midnight Oil, definitely tasty.

gmap.adr_address: 500 W 5th St, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.name: Fixe Southern House

reviews.text:
Amazing food.  The deviled egg appetizer and biscuit appetizer are both must haves.  Our group tried the Red Fish, Steak and Lobster Pot Pie.  All were delicious.  The Lobster Pot Pie was a house favorite and even as someone who isn't a big lobster eater, it was phenomenal.
We also had a banana pudding stuffed donut type thing for dessert which also was to die for.
Our group order a variety of beverages from the bar, all were exceptional.
To top it all off, we have amazing service.  Atmosphere also was very nice.  Outstanding recommendation from me.

Fixe is one of the most exceptional restaurants in all of Austin. The food, as you likely know, is tremendous. Biscuits, deviled eggs, fried chicken - all “best I’ve ever had” stuff. Where Fixe really shines though is the service. The GM, Jack, is an incredible host and made us feel like we were the only table he was talking to that night. I will definitely be back soon. Thanks again!

We were warmly welcomed and the atmosphere is wonderful. There was a great mix between casual and people dressed up and it definitely felt like an environment where you could come as you are and enjoy an amazing meal! The owner was friendly and the waiter took time to write a list of places to visit during our stay in Austin. The food was phenomenal! The biscuits and the hush puppies are to die for. You can literally see the steam coming off of the biscuits when you open them straight from the oven and they said that they butter them every 2 minutes while they are baking and that it's a labor of love. And I could tell!

James (owner and executive chef) really, really, really, really has his food on point here! I was only able to go to brunch as of 6/7/21, but the brunch was S-O-L-I-D. Whatever Fixe is using for their biscuits, dough wise, is absolute fire and the herbivore was probably the most amazing version of grits I have tasted to date. The brioche was delectable as well.
I will without a doubt, no questions asked, absolutely, be back here for dinner as there are some heavy hitter menu items I must try! I encourage you, reading this, to do the same!

Went to Fixe for breakfast and I'm so happy I did! Food was great! I ordered The Herbivore and the sweet and savory Fixe biscuit cinnamon rolls. Best cinnamon rolls I've had in a long time! My brunch drink was on point too. Met one of the owners while I was there, and he was extremely welcoming! I would highly recommend this restaurant and would definitely go back!

gmap.adr_address: 306 E 53rd St, Austin, TX 78751-2014, USA
gmap.name: Foreign & Domestic

reviews.text: We love this local place! They have a small vegan menu with tasty options. It is cozy restaurant. We love sitting at the counter; we can watch the chefs! It is a great date night option.

The food was absolutely amazing. The chef's table experience is totally worth it. They really put out the plates with such a small team and you saw that the owner/chef is really invested in putting out the best product!

First time visit to Austin. Had dinner here with my Austin pals! What a great spot! Neighborhood vibe (but on a busy street). Unpretentious— none of that ridiculous blather about all the ingredients— just friendly, competent service and very tasty flavor combinations. Wonderful selection of local beers. Impressive wine list. You won’t be disappointed. And how fab to eat outside and feel the sun on your face! (I’m from Minnesota.)
Sorry— no food photos! 🤪
Foreign & Domestic is fantastic. 5 stars.

Friendly staff and great atmosphere. Has Austin vibes all over.  We ordered the swordfish, gnocchi, pork chop, risotto and by far the pork chop was the best option.  All the food was good but everyone had to eat a piece of the pork chop, it was that good.

gmap.adr_address: Hank Ave, Austin, TX 78745, USA
gmap.name: Hank Avenue

name: Hideaway Kitchen  Bar
address: 4323 S IH 35 Frontage Rd Austin TX 78744 USA

gmap.adr_address: 4323 N Interstate 35 Frontage Rd, Austin, TX 78744, USA
gmap.formatted_address: 4323 N Interstate 35 Frontage Rd, Austin, TX 78744, USA
gmap.name: Hideaway Kitchen & Bar

reviews.text: I really liked the atmosphere and inside was cute, our food came out decently fast and I had the mushroom goat cheese burger which was exquisite, the cheese was strong but not overpowering and paired so well with the burger. Best thing was easily the fries, I wanted to grab a second order after my wife helped herself to some of mine. The biscuits and gravy was good as well though the red potatoes seemed under seasoned or just a little bland. The staff was friendly and quick, the drinks were a little confusing though, the whole self serve thing is kind of different and when it’s your first time it can be a bit confusing seating yourself and having to get your own silverware, almost like fast food style but with a sit down atmosphere. Still it was good and I think I’d try it again next time I’m in south Austin.

First time trying, I was needing to find a place near that area and decided to give Hideaway a try. I was pleasently surprised! Great vibe, both inside and outside dining. Order at the counter service and they deliver your food. Full bar and flights menu. They have food ranging from savory (friend chicken and waffles) to sweet (strawberry shortcake waffles). We went from brunch and I would go back.

If you want amazing food, amazing service this is the place to go. Our food came out promptly and our service was beyond informative and I'll definitely be back. You'll love how huge the portions are. Definitely to share with another person. They have a menu for the week and another for the weekend I went on a Monday hoping to get french toast sadly that's a weekend meal. Well I picked the waffles and my goodness what a great option it was beyond delicious. Can't wait to be back

You'd think the food would be great by the pictures but thats not entirely the case. My husband ordered the chicken fried steak and it tasted like a dirty dish rag with thyme. That's it. There is hardly any flavor in the dishes we ordered. My plate however was okay. I forced about half down before giving up. At least the servers were nice.

We went for cocktails and food after reading so many good reviews.  Well, we were told no cocktails because they were out of ice. Huh? There's a gas station one block away. Why not go get some??Strangely,  they could make a tequila sunrise though..

The food was better than expected but the floor was dirty and it looked like staff had no idea what they were doing or who was responsible for what.

Lastly,  the restroom had no soap in either dispenser and it was 7pm.

No need to return when there are so many better places around.

gmap.adr_address: 506 West Ave, Austin, TX 78701-2723, USA
gmap.name: Irene’s

reviews.text:
Great,  great food and drinks spot on downtown Austin.  Large inside and outside areas, with full bar.  Draft list is great,  great cocktails and happy hour.
Food was good,  service was fast,  and everything looked clean.  The front area has to go coffee and pastries homemade! Definitely will be back here again.

Irene's has been my favorite brunch spot since I moved to Austin three years ago. The staff is always friendly and The vibe is trendy but relaxed. If there's a long wait they have a wonderful walk-up bar where you can order $5 mimosas or $5 bloody Marys and wait on their patio. Located downtown It's just a quick stroll to some great day drinking places when you're trying to have a Sunday fun day.

100% recommend the Buffalo cauliflower, do keep in mind that the menu is semi seasonal so they change it up every now and then.
Burger sliders were on point!

Very interesting dishes, all with a unique twist. Plus a great brunch option Fri-Sun complete with specialty drinks. Food was definitely good, pricing is a bit high for what you get, setting is fairly stark, and service is average for the area. Definitely worth a visit, and appears quite popular. Just don't come here if you want straightforward, plain food options.

Delicious brunch! We sat on the side of the building where there was some nice shade.  The staff was very friendly and accommodating! We brought our dog and they were so sweet to him.

I got the migas and added bacon. It was super flavorful and the green salsa was mouthwatering.  The biscuit fritters has good flavor but we're a little burnt. My husband got the biscuit breakfast and he love it! The homemade Jelly was amazing he said and everything had a flavorful homemade taste.

gmap.adr_address: 1601 Waterston Ave, Austin, TX 78703, USA
gmap.name: Josephine House

reviews.text: Wonderful brunch experience. Small quarters but nice layout. Able to have a great conversation. The egg salad was awesome and the service was impeccable. Dined inside but when it gets cooler will go back to experience their beautiful patio.They are NOT doing curbside or online orders at this time.

DISCRIMINATION. We - two Latinos, ordered food and a few mimosas. About half way through our meal the server - Alysia, says there is a RSVP coming to our exact table (and not the TWO vacant tables nearby) and WE NEED TO LEAVE but does not suggest moving to another table as we are still consuming. The manager - Marissa (also a server),  then comes and suggest we can move to another table for an amazing 20 MORE minutes until WE NEED TO LEAVE.

FOOD WAS GREAT. BUT WE WERE NOT WELCOMED.

Highly recommended!

The cheese plate was great. We added some prosciutto to it.

We had the burger and pasta, both were delicious.

For dessert, their house-made cookies were so good.

I've been to Josephine House many times over the past year, and this place is just a solid 10/10 every time. Great staff, wonderful ambiance, and delicious food you will want to come back for. Perfect spot for a couples brunch or to bring people from out of town.

My boyfriend & I came here for a last minute birthday brunch, and we luckily snagged a table! Try to call ahead for a reservation (if you can), because this is a popular spot.. And, for good reason! Everything was amazing 🖤

name: Juliet Italian Kitchen
address: 1500 Barton Springs Rd Austin TX 78704 USA

gmap.adr_address: 1500 Barton Springs Rd, Austin, TX 78704, USA
gmap.formatted_address: 1500 Barton Springs Rd, Austin, TX 78704, USA
gmap.name: Juliet Italian Kitchen

reviews.text:
Service was great! Our waiter was on top of his game. Kudos to him!!! Outside area looks very nice and inviting.
Food 👎🏻…. Sorry to say but it just had zero taste. I grew up in Europe and have been to Italy a gazillion times growing up. This is nowhere near Italian food. Zero flavor!
I will say my husband and I would like to come back for just drinks on their patio after dinner somewhere else.
Again kudos to the amazing wait staff!

My daughter and I had dinner here last night and left a bit unsatisfied.  On the bright side, service was attentive and friendly.  The food we had one pasta dish and one pork dish was tasty for standard-fare Italian.  On the 'could use improvement' side, the ambiance was lacking - we were sitting next to a broken window that looked onto a busy street.  Interior decor was a bit sparse and sterile except for some pictures that my daughter called "creepy".   I had two glasses of different red wine (they only sell wine by the glass).  Although I didn't see the bottles or boxes that the wine was poured from, I think the price charged per glass was higher than the cost of a bottle.  (Take this from someone that drinks a LOT of wine in the $6-15/bottle range.)  The second glass of wine was oxidized.  I assume this was due to an open bottle from prior days that was not properly resealed with a vacuum cork.  In my experience, this is a common mistake with restaurants that offer several wines by the glass, but again I didn't see it being poured.

Only thing saving this place from one stars is the beautiful ambiance while dining outside. Almost $100 for two people and I got the worst spaghetti I have ever eaten, a small meatball so full of grease and yet so dry water is needed to swallow it and a warm beer that more than likely sat for 10-15 minutes before being brought to me. How in the heck does this place have such a high rating?

A must visit if you’re in the area. Their outdoor area was phenomenal we really enjoyed our visit here. Food was alright. We had the shared fungi pasta and paid additionally $8 to add chicken... I didn’t see the chicken 🤷‍♂️. Another couple ordered the posta with clams and the pasta was lacking big time... I would love to visit here again primarily for the outdoor location. If they step up the meals to match pricing it would be +5 stars.

The outdoor seating/patio is really pretty but the food is just okay... had a table for four and nobody was impressed with their food. The dishes came out a bit cold too. Maybe it’s better just for a drink?

name: La Condesa
address: 400 W 2nd St A Austin TX 78701 USA

gmap.adr_address: 400 W 2nd St A, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.formatted_address: 400 W 2nd St A, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.name: La Condesa

reviews.text: Service was good. Food was disappointing.
Great service, even better food! All food is cooked fresh and when serving, they provide a description of where it was sourced from. Excellent drinks as well. Worth the money!
Excellent place for a nice dinner out. A nice selection of items to choose from. GREAT service and food was served hot and fresh! I'll be back!
Came to this place for happy hour and was not disappointed! The food was great and the staff was super friendly! Definitely would recommend since it’s right in downtown!
Great authentic mexican food. Really like the homemade corn tortillas, guac, and mole. The hand-made tacos are also delicious.

deals.item: 2 Oz Pours Of Whisky For The Price Of A 1 Oz Pour

gmap.adr_address: 401 W 2nd St, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.name: Lamberts

reviews.text:
My friends and I went to Lamberts on our first night in Austin, in search of a great entry to barbecue in Texas! I'm a little bummed to say Lamberts missed the mark for us.

As far as the location itself, it was a generally nice building and it was really great that they had reservations available (when many barbecue places often don't). However... when arriving at the restaurant, our table wasn't ready at our reservation time so we ended up waiting for 15-20 minutes. Not really the end of the world, but it was a little disappointing, and the staff recommended that we get drinks at the bar... which would be great if there was space to hang out by the bar or in the waiting area.

Onto the actual food & drink experience: the drinks were solid and we all tried various cocktails and didn't have any bad experiences there. The food itself is one of my bigger qualms with Lamberts -- quality is OK but quantity is really not there for what you're paying. I understand the appeal of an upscale barbecue restaurant, where the ambiance is nice and you can get a table indoors, but it just didn't seem like you were remotely getting your value for money here with the food (both the main dishes and the entrees). Portions are small, and the quality is *just* ok, especially compared to some of the more notorious barbecue spots in Austin (which provide better taste and quantity for less $$).

Service was solid and the staff was nice overall -- they made their best efforts to overcome any challenges of the evening.

In general, I'll say you can probably find a better barbecue spot in Austin than Lamberts if you're really looking for good taste and good value for money. if you're really looking to get the ambiance of a cozy restaurant and get some decent (but expensive) barbecue, Lamberts could work just fine for that purpose.

Great space for networking.  Enjoyed the Cobb salad and sides.. mac n cheese was amazing and fresh broccoli had a little kick to it.. which was nice.  Desserts didn't pan out to well but I'll give them a try on another day.  Service was great!

Yes, great BBQ, all of it!….. for those who don’t mind paying for overpriced food. I loved their side dishes-macaroni and mashed potatoes.
They have a nice bar at the front entrance where we sat while waiting for our table. I guess it can be a nice place to eat when celebrating a special occasion.

Different but very good. I would call it gourmet BBQ. Very tender, high quality, and spot on. Very cool historical building located downtown. Also a very high end bar. Servers were very good and polite and did a great job. The brisket was so tender and the ribs fell off the bone.

Thank you Lamberts.  Wish you had a location in San Diego, California.   My wife loved the clam appetizers.  The 3 meat Bar B Que sampler was awesome!  We had ribs, brisket and sausage. All of the meats were full of flavor and fall off the bone tenderness.  The meats didn't need a traditional sauce. A side of mustard was brilliant. The dinning area was just another comment to great food and service.  We sat a the bar and had great time.  Our bartender was helpful and responsive.  Can't wait to tell our friends and family in California.

deals.item: House Wine White, Red, Rosé Glass/bottle
When I Dip, You Dip, We Dip

gmap.adr_address: 1401 W 6th St, Austin, TX 78703, USA
gmap.name: Nightcap

reviews.text: If I could give them more star I would. The staff was awesome and very polite. My wife and I was given a true VIP treatment. The food was, in my opinion, 5 star restaurant quality with the quantity of places like Cracker Barrel. We we graced by our new friend Christin Rowan, thank you so much. The food is heavenly, Drew, you're just amazing. The overall feel of the place is what you'd imagine if you when to a gourmet party house. It's hard to explain, just go.

Really delicious food and equally great drinks. The overall ambiance of the restaurant is very relaxing and casual. The decor is very pretty and the restaurant location isn’t in a super busy area. Service was great. Definitely more expensive for their main course items but they also have a decent happy hour.

So all I can say is that everything was amazing! The food service, and location were perfect. I recommend the kitchen sink salad. Artichoke and pimento dip and hoagie. You won't go wrong. Two thumbs up.

Nightcap is my new favorite spot in downtown Austin. The vibe and food go hand in hand. It truly is a restaurant in its own category. Try the nightcap burger, you will thank me later. The drinks are amazing and the guest DJs play the soundtrack to your life while you’re there! Highly recommend this place!

Always a pleasure, been coming to visit this weekend establishment for the last couple of months, we were referred by friends whom are now family. The staff and food is great. Perfect for a dinner with friends, date night, or brunch with live music. There is also a DJ that visits frequently on the weekends. Check out the menu and see for yourself. The owner and chef are amazing. Well worth the prices. So take a group of your favorite peeps and head out

gmap.adr_address: 3411 Glenview Ave, Austin, TX 78703, USA
gmap.name: Olive & June

reviews.text: Such a cute vibe. The food and staff were wonderful. We requested certain accommodations for some of our plates and they went above and beyond for our table. The kindest, most personable staff. I can’t say enough good things about the food—everything from the appetizers to dessert was phenomenal. Looking forward to visiting again soon!

The staff was welcoming and attentive from the moment we walked in. Our server was friendly and delivered a fantastic experience throughout the entire meal. She answered all of our questions about the menu and provided us with some wonderful recommendations.
The atmosphere was perfect for a casual dinner date. Food presentation was beautiful and the fresh ingredients made for a memorable meal.

Loved this place!
Dined at the bar. Alex rocks! Knew all about the cocktails and wine. Easy to talk to...which is icing on the cake. Try the Bucatini (spell?).
Amazing food - so delish!
The best Italian food experience in Austin.

gmap.adr_address: 208 W 4th St, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.name: Péché

reviews.text: I’m surprised by some of the poor reviews. We could not have had a better experience. The drinks were fun and adventurous. The bartender answered all of our questions, and made excellent suggestions. Everything we ate was truly a journey. The chef also came to our table, and was extremely personable. He made several recommendations, and we were not disappointed. Will definitely return!!

For date night, we chose Péché and I'm glad we did! There were candles at every table and up at the bar, they have gorgeous chandeliers and wall fixtures that really create a whole vibe.

They have amazing happy hour specials and drinks; I love that there's a gigantic wall of alcohol behind the bar, so much that the bartenders need ladders to get to everything; I was impressed to say the least.

I had a Tiki Soda and a Daiquiri…both made with rum and both super delicious! My appetizer was the Mac
& Cheese with Gruyere and Duck…I was mesmerized - and with it being on the happy hour menu, I highly recommend!

I didn’t get to take a picture of it, but the short ribs with mashed potatoes and mushrooms made my night! The meat was so tender, juicy and was just as good the best day when I ate my leftovers.

They were pretty busy for it being Thursday at 6:30 but I understand that their happy hour is very popular. Our appetizers came out pretty quick, but We didn’t end up getting our entrees until a little after an hour after we ordered and our second drinks took almost as long. This doesn’t take away from their great food and service, I just suggest going during a less busy time.

We spent around $70 per person here and got every dollars worth. I definitely look forward to coming back for happy hour.

Great cocktails and food in a very vintage almost speakeasy style building, low lighting but fast paced music. Dress up or dress casual it is a mix of both.
The food was amazing and I was able to get something gluten free, I ordered the duck breast which was cooked to perfection and very flavorful along with the veggies. I will say they seemed a bit short staffed for a Sunday night, our waiter was on top of things but the food took a while, we just enjoyed our cocktails while waiting.

My wife, daughter and I chose Peche' to celebrate our anniversary and we couldn't be happier that we did.  This traditional French brasserie restaurant offers a wide range of French meals including a long list of daily specials.  We started with a deviled egg dish and an assorted meat/pate' tray.  For mains, I opted for the beef cheek special while my wife chose one of the duck dishes.  All of the dishes we had were delicious and superbly prepared and presented.  Dish pricing was very reasonable, especially considering the effort required.  The wine list was suitably broad and also reasonably priced.  Our server was friendly, attentive and knowledgeable.  The ambiance was comfortable and interesting - very much like I have seen nice brasseries in France or Manhattan.  We wrapped things up with a few deserts with me opting for the pecan pie.  This was nothing less than an excellent dining experience.  I would love to return soon!

If I could give them 10 Stars I would.  Came here on whim on Father's Day and had one of the best dining experiences ever.  Very friendly staff (ask for ERIC as he's a doll), and the food was top notch.  Some of the best mac n cheese I've ever eaten.  Try the bananas foster dessert- you won't go wrong.

name: Perla
address: 1400 S Congress Ave Austin TX 78704 USA

gmap.adr_address: 1512 E 6th St, Austin, TX 78702-3306, USA
gmap.name: La Perla Bar

reviews.text: Amazing service! So grateful to Mark Tafoya & his staff Rosie!  They are incredibly to work with we just hosted an event here a corporate morning mixer & it was great! Great food, great service & a wonderful setting. Authentic Mexican cuisine & a great cultural experience overall! Support local businesses!

Loved my experience here! We had Rae as our server and I'm obsessed! Her amazing energy carried throughout our experience, from bringing our drinks fast to recommending super yummy dishes, we will definitely be returning! Thanks again water tower!
The live band was a nice treat. Friendly staff along with reasonably priced menu items, made for a fun date night. Great music and dancing. We will be going back.

Sadly I can't rate the food, we just had nachos and drinks. The nachos were very tasty and the Margarita is the best I've ever tasted. I will definitely go back and have some more during future visits.

This was a nice change from all the French food we had been having. We went on a Saturday night around 830 and it was very crowded. Most people were drinking but there were some people like us that had dinner. The food was good and so were the margaritas.

name: Scholz Garten
address: 1607 San Jacinto Blvd Austin TX 78701 USA

gmap.adr_address: 1607 San Jacinto Blvd, Austin, TX 78701-1414, USA
gmap.formatted_address: 1607 San Jacinto Blvd, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.name: Scholz Garten

reviews.text: I don't know much about the inside of this establishment since I was there to play the fiddle and mostly stayed by the outdoor stage. The staff was super friendly and the outdoor seating area was fairly large with lots of shady spots. I did order the watermelon salad and it was great! The other band-peoples enjoyed their choices from the menu, as well!

Love Schulz beer garden. Great place to have beers and listen to live music on their patio. Their menu has changed over the years, but current offering has tasty German food(sausages, schnitzel, killer giant pretzel) plus the standard American burgers etc. Street parking only which can be tough when busy.

We loved this place and the bartender who takes so much pride in the history. Wish I could remember her name. She shared the history of the original bar, the secret trap door with tunnel to the capitol building, the photos of the owner and even the paintings of the woman and man on the restroom doors (a beloved waitress from the 1970’s and one of her loyal customers). Live music was great, food was excellent, and our server gave great recommendations.

I visited this place on a Saturday night. We sat outside because we had the dog with us. The waiter was very personable and recommended some things. We ordered the potato pancakes and they were delicious. I ordered the Scholz Burger with bacon and avacado. It was huge! It came with crispy waffle fries that were warm when they came out. The burger was delicious. I could only eat half after eating the potato pancake. My son got the sausage sample plate. It came with three different links of sausage, a little cup of sauerkraut and a cup of something made from red cabbage. There were three different kinds of mustard too. He said it was very good. There was music playing, but not too loudly that you couldn't hear each other speak. The waiter brought out a bowl of water for our dog too. I recommend this restaurant.

Went for lunch. Nice old school feel to it. Clean. Easy to have a conversation (not loud). Young waiter was friendly. I was happy to finally be eating french fries after a three day search at other restaurants, and although they were just ok, it was the hamburger that came with that I enjoyed the most. I left feeling satisfied.

gmap.adr_address: 440 W 2nd St, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.name: She’s Not Here

reviews.text: I had the coffee pork with coconut rice and macaroni salad. For dessert I had the coconut cake. The pork was absolutely spectacular. I am not normally a fan of cold pasta salad, but I enjoyed the macaroni salad. I am definitely a dessert person, and this cake did not disappoint me whatsoever.only because everything else including the rice was so delicious that I did not have enough room was I able to take some of it home to my husband who loved it so much he couldn't stop thanking me for bringing him from home to try. I strongly recommend going to the restaurant "She's Not Here". I had a barrel-aged cocktail made from scotch and banana liqueur with other liquors, this cocktail was unique and delicious. It sounds like everything I tried has the descriptor delicious, that would be correct.the staff was also very friendly and helpful without being overbearing even though the crowd at the time I visited was light.

This place is too expensive and has tiny portions. We went in for lunch on a Friday at noon and they were out of one of the main dishes (menu was very small to start with). Then we ordered a different plate but not everyone got it because they also ran out of it. Appetizers came in at different times. One dish was too spicy for some people and there is no warning on the menu. Would not recommend this place.

I love this place. It feels like I just walked into another country, and possibly another decade...Kind of like some place South Pacific, during WWII.  Drinks and food exceeded expectation in flavor and appearance. Seating is comfortable/cool with a multitude of options, including an outdoor patio. Only drawback is that they close for a couple hours between lunch and dinner... I hate that.
She's Mot There recently switched over to a new Vietnamese inspired menu. It's fantastic! Ambience is great, service is excellent, and food is delicious!

When we walked in all three of us made separate comments about how cool/beautiful/eclectic this place was.  Everyone we spoke to was very friendly, I even got a apology for the waitress startling me by filling up my water on the sneak (kudos BTW!).  The sushi tasted fresh and was delivered very promptly.  The big portions of food didn't seem that big but with sushi appetizers it was enough to split and not over indulge ourselves.
Definitely recommending to our friends and for our next group dinner.

gmap.adr_address: Swift Building, 315 Congress Ave, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.formatted_address: Swift Building, 315 Congress Ave, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.name: Swift's Attic

reviews.text: My husband and I went there for a night out together. We both loved it. We searched for a romantic place, this restaurant was well recommended for it. There were a couple of couples there, but also some group of friends around. They have a good selection of drinks for who enjoys alcohol. We are not on alcohol anymore, but we still loved the ambience. I am vegetarian, so we ended up sharing the vegetarians options, they also accommodate putting the meat on the side for one of the salads we chose. Our favorite was the risotto, it was divine. We like to explore different places, but we will definitely go back to this one.

Had our anniversary dinner here and it was amazing. We made friends with our neighbors. The food and drinks were amazing. We ordered the bacon wrapped apricot - twice. The ice ball drinks were fun and delicious, you just have to wait a little until the ice melts!

Would recommend for a great dinner.

Amazing experience. Surprised my husband here for his birthday. The whole group loved it. Loved the idea of ordering a bunch of plates and sharing them. We got to try so much. My favorite part was the dessert, if you are visiting you must try it. Just show the picture that I posted it is one of my favorite dessert I’ve ever had.

Husband and I went here recently and everything was amazing. Great atmosphere and place for a nice date. Their food and drinks were delicious and inventive. We had their vegan pad Thai which was my favorite thing we had. I wish there was more. Service was also great. Please go visit Swift’s attic!

Atmosphere, drinks, and staff are great.
We stopped in randomly because I looked on the menu and saw it had a Happy Hour on a Saturday from 4-5:30pm. Incentive and a surprise, so why not.

Got the bill and the drinks were all full price, I asked if Happy Hour on the website is incorrect, she said no and offered to fix the bill.
She came back with my card, swiped, and ready to sign... but only marked the wine as Happy Hour. The other drinks I ordered (last one ordered well before the end of Happy Hour) are clearly on the Happy Hour menu.

Your business chose to have a Happy Hour, it states it on your website and it was not rang in properly or fixed. I feel like that is to rack up my bill. It is not okay no matter what I can afford, this is what your business offers.

gmap.adr_address: 307 W 5th St, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.name: The Roosevelt Room

reviews.text: This was our favorite place when we visited Austin. Their happy hour was so great. Their cocktails were absolutely out of this world and we are very picky about our cocktails. The service was impeccable as well. Definitely give this place a visit if you want some good appetizers and cocktails!

Went for happy hour, drinks were fairly priced. My banana daiquiri was tasty. Felt a bit rushed by the staff even though we still had time left on our reservation. And they were out of spiked ice cream but overall nice vibes.

The Roosevelt Room vastly exceeded my expectations. This is SO MUCH MORE than just a speakeasy-style bar. This is an extremely classy, professional, and expert-level drinking experience. The cocktails here were so refined and perfected, and the staff were so immensely talented and entertaining. While I'm sure it's amazing for groups of any size, I'd ESPECIALLY recommend the Roosevelt Room if you're looking for a sexy, romantic couple's experience, especially if you can sit at the bar and have your bartender right in front of you. We were from out-of-town and this was probably the highlight of our entire trip.

Pleasant and fun speakeasy atmosphere. Large list of cocktails, both Roosevelt Room originals and their refinements of classics. All the drinks our group had were well crafted and quite tasty. There are also a number of nonalcoholic cocktails--we didn't try any but they looked to be of equal quality. The waitress was quite knowledgeable about all their selections, and clearly enjoyed helping customers find the cocktail to fit their taste and mood. The only caveat I would provide is that the ambiance includes very low lighting, which is on point for the decor, but could be an impediment to some. Overall a great place for a romantic date, or for larger groups having fun--they have seating for both. I highly recommend reservations, especially for a large party.

We have never had a bad experience at The Roosevelt Room. My husband is making his way through the drink passport and in I am thoroughly enjoying all things rum there. The staff is incredible and always gives great recommendations. Always a fun way to spend a few hours of our weekend.

gmap.adr_address: 400 Colorado St, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.name: Truluck's Ocean's Finest Seafood and Crab

reviews.text:
My brother and I treated my Mom (and Dad) for her birthday (on a Friday evening) and had the best experience! Live music, gorgeous interior, great location, world-class staff and service, and the food was to die for. We were able to call ahead and speak directly to the beverage manager to request a chilled bottle waiting at the table. He was able to give us a recommendation based on our mom’s preference and they had everything ready when we arrived.  Many of the staff made it a point to remember my mom’s name before we arrived (which we mentioned in our reservation) and wish her a happy birthday (even those that weren’t our direct servers) which made my mom feel so special. They took their time to go through the menu, make recommendations, were so attentive to us the entire time we were there, and didn’t make us feel rushed at all. Truly an exceptional and elevated evening that I would recommend to anyone looking for an unforgettable experience!

Update: The manager even followed up the next day to ask about our experience and make sure we were satisfied. Exceeded expectations in every way!

We arrived at 8PM without a reservation and were greeted by the amazing Maître d' Andrew!  Not only did he graciously welcome us and introduce himself to us, he gave us a couple of options as to where we could sit.  He then effortlessly turned us over to his serving team and we enjoyed a fantastic dining experience.  Of course, the food and the service was impeccable (thanks to Brittany especially!) but easily the most memorable part of the evening at Truluck's was the way Andrew cared for us at the outset!  We look forward to our next dinner at Truluck's and to watching Andrew work his magic!  My bet is that he'll remember my name!

Wow! I've never been so happy to hand over $200 on dinner. The food was perfect and the service was like nothing I've ever seen. The staff coordinated to make our experience seamless. The valet even had our car waiting as we exited. I am impressed!

My girlfriend and I had an exceptional anniversary dinner here! The staff made wonderful recommendations, and the ambiance was perfect. The drinks and food are well worth the price. You'll love this place for any occasion!
Celebrated my birthday nic restaurant 👍

gmap.adr_address: 400 Colorado St, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.name: Truluck's Ocean's Finest Seafood and Crab

Celebrated my birthday nic restaurant 👍

name: Uchiko
address: 4200 N Lamar Blvd Austin TX 78756 USA

deals.item: Pali Wine Co Riveria Pinot Noir

gmap.adr_address: 4200 N Lamar Blvd, Austin, TX 78756, USA
gmap.formatted_address: 4200 N Lamar Blvd, Austin, TX 78756, USA
gmap.name: Uchiko

reviews.text:
Had a great time here. The atmosphere inside was modern and chill which made me feel comfortable enough to be there for almost two hours. On top of that, the service was quick and consistently good. The waitress helped me out with some great recommendations and definitely made the experience much better (I find big menus with no pictures to be very overwhelming).

As for the food, My partner and I had some oysters, a few courses of sushi, which we thought were good, but none of them mind-blowing, and finally a short rib that was out-of-this-word-delicious. Following the entrees, we ordered a couple of desserts that were equally divine.

While expensive for pretty small portions, I can definitely recommend coming here for any special occasion, if not just for the desserts!

We couldn't ask for a more perfect place to celebrate our son's birthday.  Our server Jeremy recommended the most spectacular dishes and the sake was amazing. Hard to pick our favorites because we enjoyed everything we ate. Thank you for these precious memories we will cherish forever.  Looking forward to returning soon.

Came here for date night and our server Shelby was absolutely fabulous! Rating 4 stars for the limited drink selection, but wanted to write this review for Shelby who really knew her stuff! Wonderful recommendations great attitude. Took the time to get to know us and surprised us with perfectly matched dishes! One of the best customer service situations I've ever had at a restaurant

Too much deliciousness! We had multiple plates and shared everything but nothing was bad. One of the few or rare times I've eaten that much and wanted more. Food, ambiance  and staff all wonderful! I will return soon!

An amazing sushi restaurant. Their indoor sitting is stunning and the service was great. I had to make a reservation weeks in advance to get into their sake social (happy hour) which is so worth it. My partner and I spend a little over $80 and ended ordering at least half of the happy hour menu. Every dish was so flavorful and unique. The nigiri was delicious. Highly recommend.

gmap.adr_address: 4222 Duval St, Austin, TX 78751, USA
gmap.name: Uncle Nicky's Italian Specialties

reviews.text: As a long time Austinite and Hyde Park resident, I was so sad to see Dolce Vita close. Uncle Nicky's carries the torch with a similar, but even better (IMO) selection of casual Italian treats. I most appreciate that they didn't go nuts with the pricing like so many new Austin places do... great way to guarantee loyal neighborhood regulars. The weekend brunch is also great, and really flying under the radar.

Looking for a quiet place with outdoor seating on a Saturday, i remembered seeing great reviews for this place. We got a spicy capicola sandwich and the turkey sandwich and a cocktail. Both sandwiches were bland, not toasted, the turkey sandwich was kinda wet and not particularly nice, the cocktail was ok. Also they only take card. Not worth coming back.

Update: The dish was still very tasty despite looking quite a bit different than the menu item.

I expected to get dishes matching their photos. For example in their photos of the pane shows multiple layers of prosciutto and brightly colored green zucchini that covered the bread. This didn’t match what we got!

There is about half the amount of prosciutto compared to the photos and the zucchini doesn’t even cover the bread. So the restaurant delivered the correct amount of bread but half the toppings. Not cool!
Tasty sandwich, but small. Almost $20 for a spicy capicola sandwich, lays chips, and a coffee after 20% tip. Won't get lunch there again, it's just too expensive for what it is.
Nice service. The best meatballs in Austin. Sandwiches left something to be desired, and the chopped salad was very underwhelming.

gmap.adr_address: 4807 Airport Blvd, Austin, TX 78751, USA
gmap.name: Vamonos

reviews.text:
Awesome place! Food was yummy! We had the taco salad and chilaquiles. The salsa is amazing! It was very fresh with lots of veggies, had a kick but that didn't linger. I enjoyed it so much I ordered extra and added it all over my salad :) Super friendly and attentive staff. Our server was named Laura and she was so nice. She let us rattle off all of our special instructions for our orders (we are dairy and gluten free so we may come off as a pain in the butt to some). She just smiled and assured us it was all good. Food came out perfect and delicious! Sorry we didn't take pictures but it was too good to wait!!!

We're moving soon and considering this neighborhood. If we do land here, we'll for sure be back!
I was super impressed. The food was so tasty! Pro tip for vegetarians: most of their sauces contain meat... their queso does too. Make sure you remind them to keep the sauce vegetarian too.

Food can best be summed up here as inoffensive, but uninspired. Margaritas are a good deal during happy hour. Queso, refried beans, and beef enchiladas were bland. Salsa was sweeter than it was spicy. Unless something major changes regarding the menu, I won't be back.

Saw some good reviews online and stopped in for lunch - so glad we did because this place is amazing!! I had the skirt steak ranch tacos and I wish I had a bigger appetite so I could’ve ordered a second plate! 10/10 would come here again
Queso is outstanding. Rice and beans are not just sides..really good. And the salsa is fantastic

gmap.adr_address: 200 Lavaca St, Austin, TX 78701, USA
gmap.name: W Austin

reviews.text:
It was a nice hotel, breakfast was really good, great pancakes! I'm not sure if it's worth the money paid to stay there. MAJOR UPDATE: 2021

Update on the hotel. Such a fantastic place to stay. We were there Jan 2021 celebrating my birthday, back in Feb, and heading back this coming Sat. We had an amazing stay, the room was fantastic along with the view. Seems like there were many upgrades, staff is amazing, very accommodating and easy to work with. Absolutely recommend it for celebrations, stay-cays, and networking events.

For my birthday weekend we decided to stay here. They took great care of my husband and I. The pool was beautiful and the staff was great. The room was clean and stocked with great supplies. The food wasn't as warm as I would have liked but it was on point with flavor.

We had a wonderful stay at W Austin! The rooms are clean and well-appointed. The staff were very helpful. When we reported a maintenance issue with our shower they promptly switched our room and gave us an upgrade in the process! The location is phenomenal just downtown and very close to so many great restaurants and music venues. We will definitely recommend W Austin to our friends and family!
Generally stay here when we come into town. Great pool and their gym is better than most 24s. Definitely worth visiting. Super central location.

This was my first time staying at a W hotel. For the price of the hotel, I was expecting a bit more of an experience, but it was just average. The lobby feel very disjointed, not open at all, and makes you feel quite cramped. Our room was upgraded, which we very much appreciated as we were celebrating our anniversary and it made it that much more special, but other than the view, it was just an average room. It's not that we had a bad experience, nothing terrible happened, it was clean, but it just felt like it should have been nicer for the nightly rate as compared to other hotels in the city.
